author: buffalonews
title: West Side Rowing Club teams have a big day
text:
The West Side Rowing Club and West Side Rowing Campus teams (City Honors, Mount Saint Mary’s and St. Joe’s) had to do a little extra packing for their trip home from Rochester on Sunday. They brought back 18 medals – including four golds – from the Head of the Genesee competition.
St. Joe’s Men’s Four took home the gold in a time of 16 minutes, 49.79 seconds. On the team were Charlie Kwitchoff, August Cudeck, Charles Pratt, Eric Seaner and Charlie Ivancic. West Side’s Men’s High School team finished third in that event. St. Joe’s also won the Men’s High School Second Eights in 16:24.8, and the Men’s Frosh Eights in 18:40.27. City Honors took the Men’s HS Second Eights in 25:56.8.
The West Side Men’s HS Eight came in second in its final, finishing two seconds behind. On the team were Matthew O’Connor, David Gee, Eli Swing, John Saunders, Michael Shrader, Noah Munoz, Joshua Hobika, Ian Shea, and Rani Patel. St. Joe’s crew was fourth in that event.
St. Joe’s also picked up a silver medal in the Men’s HS Novice Fours, and bronze medals in the Men’s HS Lightweight Fours and the Men’s HS Second Fours.
In the Women’s HS Eights race, West Side (Emma Vicaretti, Hanna Prince, Samantha Lazar, Sophia Castillo, Lila Evans, Brigitte Vossler, Erin Shea, Stefani Shultz, and Kathryn Holmwood) took silver, just one second ahead of third-place Mount Saint Mary’s. In the Women’s HS Fours, West Side and City Honors finished second and third respectively. City Honors also took second in the Women’s Second HS Fours.
Mount Saint Mary’s took home two more medals in the Women’s Frosh Eights (silver) and Women’s HS Pairs (bronze). The West Side HS Second Eight (bronze) and West Side Women’s Masters Fours (Bronze) rounded out the medals.
